  "summary": "The heat $q$ that flows into a sample raises its temperature in proportion to its mass and its specific heat capacity $c$. Multiplying mass (grams) by $c$ (energy per gram per degree) by the temperature change (degrees) leaves an energy — the machine confirms $q$ and $m c \\Delta T$ share the dimension of energy. This is the first rung of the energy ledger.",
